JOHANNESBURG - Two people were left in a critical condition on Tuesday morning, when a truck crashed into the back of a car on the N12 outside of Klerksdorp, paramedics said.ER24 said before noon, paramedics and local services arrived on the scene where they found a man and a woman trapped inside of the car. Fire fighters had to use specialised rescue equipment to free them from the wreckage. Once freed, they found that both the occupants sustained critical injuries, said ER24.ER24 said an emergency helicopter was called to the scene to airlift the woman to Lenmed Hospital and the man was treated on the scene for his injuries and later rushed to Potchefstroom Provincial Hospital for further treatment.The driver of the truck was assessed on the scene, but found to have sustained no injuries.The exact cause for the collision is not yet known. Local authorities attended the scene.Africa News Agency